info.description: Sophomore at UC San Diego, B.S Computer Science 2020

projects.title: Personal Website
projects.subtitle: UCSD CAT 125
description: Wrote a personal portfolio site in React and Semantic UI, hosted on Github Pages.
Wrote custom components in React for dynamic filtering of projects by tags. (you're seeing this right now!)

projects.title: Halecoin
projects.subtitle: HackUCI 2018
description: Won 'Best Overall Hack' & 'Best Social Hack' at HackUCI 2018 for a new Ethereum-based cryptocoin mined by doing exercise.
Implemented an asynchronous pushup detection algorithm in Node.js, parsing real-time data from OpenPose, a deep learning library which extracts motion capture data from real-time webcam input.
Implemented exponential running average on detection algorithm output for callbacks to Firebase backend.
Worked on React front-end for demo of proof-of-concept during hackathon judging stage.

projects.title: Pex
projects.subtitle: SBHacks 2018
description: Collected data and trained a linear classifier in Tensorflow to recognize exercise forms, obtaining ~95% accuracy.

Wrote an interface in Python between the classifier and open-source real-time monocular pose detection library OpenPose, towards providing real-time form checking for first-time gym goers without fitness coaches.

projects.title: BusBoss
projects.subtitle: LAHacks 2017
description: Created & demoed a statistical model for estimating turnout of hackathon participants, for better estimation of bus capacity needs to facilitate improved provision of transportation.

projects.title: The People Walk

projects.title: Rote

projects.title: DoCloud
